last_action: To Coms. on RLS. and E., R., & C.A.

title: University of California.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by amending, repealing, and adding Section 9 of Article IX thereof, relating to the University of California.
last_action: From committee with author's amendments. Read second time. Amended. Re-referred to Com. on RLS.

title: Transportation Investment Fund.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by amending Section 1 of Article XIX B thereof, relating to transportation.
last_action: From committee without further action.

title: State budget.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by amending Section 9 of Article II thereof, by amending Sections 8 and 12 of Article IV thereof, and by amending Section 3 of Article XIII A thereof, relating to the state budget.
last_action: From print. May be acted upon on or after June 29.

title: Revised biennial session.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by amending, repealing, and adding Sections 3, 8, 10, 11, and 12 of Article IV thereof, by amending, repealing, and adding Section 6 of Article XIX thereof, and by amending, repealing, and adding Section 1 of Article XIX A thereof, relating to legislative sessions.
last_action: From committee without further action.

title: Food safety: antibiotics.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by adding Article X C thereto, relating to food safety.
last_action: From print. May be acted upon on or after July 24.

title: Legislature: term limits.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by amending Section 2 of, and adding Section 2.5 to, Article IV thereof, and by amending Section 7 of Article XX thereof, relating to the Legislature.
last_action: From print. May be acted upon on or after August 23.

title: Legislature: revised biennial sessions and part-time
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by amending Section 8 of Article III thereof, by amending, repealing, and adding Sections 3, 7, 7.5, 8, 10, 11, and 12 of Article IV thereof, by amending, repealing, and adding Section 6 of Article XIX thereof, and by amending, repealing, and adding Section 1 of Article XIX A thereof, relating to the Legislature.
last_action: From print. May be acted upon on or after September 24.

title: University of California: mandatory systemwide fees.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by amending Section 9 of Article IX thereof, relating to the University of California.
last_action: Set, second hearing. Failed passage in committee. (Ayes 2. Noes 2. Page 3296.) Reconsideration granted.

title: Death penalty appeals: transfer.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by amending Section 12 of Article VI thereof, relating to death penalty appeals.
last_action: Returned to Secretary of Senate pursuant to Joint Rule 62(a). (Page 3603.)

title: State Auditor: duties.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by adding Section 10 to Article III thereof, relating to state audits.
last_action: Set, first hearing. Failed passage in committee. (Ayes 2. Noes 3. Page 3861.) Reconsideration granted.

title: Health care coverage.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by adding Section 32 to Article I thereof, relating to health care coverage.
last_action: Set, first hearing. Failed passage in committee. (Ayes 3. Noes 6. Page 3466.)

title: Legislature: bill notice requirements.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by amending Section 8 of Article IV thereof, relating to the Legislature.
last_action: From committee with author's amendments. Read second time. Amended. Re-referred to Com. on RLS.

title: Property taxation: intercounty base year value transfers.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by amending subdivision (a) of Section 2 of Article XIII A thereof, relating to taxation.
last_action: To Coms. on REV. & TAX. and E., R., & C.A.

title: Education finance.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by adding Section 8.3 to Article XVI thereof, relating to education finance.
last_action: From committee without further action.

title: Legislature: Budget Bill: passage requirements.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by amending Section 12 of Article IV thereof, relating to the Legislature.
last_action: From print. May be acted upon on or after June 5.

title: State finance.
description: A resolution directing the Secretary of State to withdraw from the consideration of the people of the State of California Senate Constitutional Amendment No. 30 (Resolution Chapter 167 of the Statutes of 2008) and further directing the Secretary of State to make amendments in Senate Constitutional Amendment No. 13 (Resolution Chapter 144 of the Statutes of 2008).
last_action: From committee without further action.

title: Expenditure limit.
description: A resolution to propose to the people of the State of California an amendment to the Constitution of the State, by repealing and adding Article XIII B thereof, and by amending Section 8.5 of Article XVI thereof, relating to expenditure limits.
last_action: From print. May be acted upon on or after September 30.
